rounds.event: The Treaty of Versailles takes effect, officially ending World War I for all combatant nations except the United States.
births: Roberto M. Levingston, Argentinian general and politician, 36th President of Argentina
deaths: Sali Nivica, Albanian journalist and politician

rounds.event: The first General Assembly of the United Nations assembles in the Methodist Central Hall, Westminster. Fifty-one nations are represented.
The New England Journal of Medicine publishes the letter Addiction Rare in Patients Treated with Narcotics, which is later misused to downplay the general risk of addiction to opioids.

rounds.event: New York: Automobile Club of America installs signs on major highways.

rounds.event: Sandinista Daniel Ortega becomes president of Nicaragua and vows to continue the transformation to socialism and alliance with the Soviet Union and Cuba; American policy continues to support the Contras in their revolt against the Nicaraguan government.
